#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/classes/class_editorinspectorplugin.rst:23
msgid ""
"When an object is edited, the :ref:`can_handle "
"<class_EditorInspectorPlugin_method_can_handle>` function is called and "
"must return ``true`` if the object type is supported."
msgstr ""

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/classes/class_editorinspectorplugin.rst:25
msgid ""
"If supported, the function :ref:`parse_begin "
"<class_EditorInspectorPlugin_method_parse_begin>` will be called, "
"allowing to place custom controls at the beginning of the class."
msgstr ""

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/classes/class_editorinspectorplugin.rst:27
msgid ""
"Subsequently, the :ref:`parse_category "
"<class_EditorInspectorPlugin_method_parse_category>` and "
":ref:`parse_property <class_EditorInspectorPlugin_method_parse_property>`"
" are called for every category and property. They offer the ability to "
"add custom controls to the inspector too."
msgstr ""

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/classes/class_editorinspectorplugin.rst:29
msgid ""
"Finally :ref:`parse_end <class_EditorInspectorPlugin_method_parse_end>` "
"will be called."
msgstr ""

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/classes/class_editorinspectorplugin.rst:31
msgid "On each of these calls, the \"add\" functions can be called."
msgstr ""

